You are building the TECH AIM ARMS website — a precision measurement and performance analytics platform for shooting sports.

Tech stack: Next.js 15, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, Framer Motion, GSAP, Three.js / React Three Fiber, shadcn/ui, Recharts.

Brand rules:
- Company name: TECH AIM ARMS
- Positioning: Analytics platform first, hardware second
- Background: #050505
- Surfaces: #111111 (panel), #1A1A1A (elevated), #232323 (secondary)
- Brand Crimson #A80038: buttons, links, active nav, CTAs, highlights
- Signal Red #BF1919: alerts, destructive, scoring rings
- Telemetry Blue #3B82F6: charts, analytics, telemetry overlays, live data only
- Text: #F5F5F5 headings, #C7CBD1 body, #8B919A muted; JetBrains Mono for data/code
- Fonts: Sora headings, Inter body
- Aesthetic: cinematic engineering UI, instrumentation overlays, angular geometry
- Avoid rounded-xl buttons, gaming aesthetics, military/tactical themes
- Maintain WCAG AA contrast (crimson CTAs use #F5F5F5 foreground)

Always use TypeScript interfaces, cn() utility, Framer Motion for UI animation, GSAP for scroll choreography, mobile-first responsive design.

Asset paths: follow `public/images/README.md`; register in `lib/imageRegistry.ts` after `npm run optimize:images`; use `@/components/media` (never hardcode `/images/` or `/models/` in components).
